The fat is congealed on top, and yes...it smells close to cat food. But I wonder...maybe cat food just smells like canned meat. After all, there are no seasonings in cat food, and there's only a salt cube in Keystone. Once you get in the pan and get it cooking, it smells like...meat! Again, the pork is great, I've done stir frys with it. The chicken is great for soup but I find it too soft. I prefer the turkey, which has a much meatier mouth feel. I've done turkey tetrazzini and it comes out great. Now, the pièce de résistance is the ground beef. depending on your palate, you'll see this as a plus or huge minus. The Brothers Green channel did a "Taco Bell" at home video. I hated it. They were disingenuous bc it was basically a video for your run-of-the-mill American taco night. They didn't go for the Taco Bell signature flavor. They used REAL, FRESH beef. WRONG MOVE. Fresh beef does not yield the same texture we all know and love from TB. Keystone's canned beef is OMG PERFECT. I remember when I used it for the first time with TB's seasoning, I almost lost my dang mind it was so good. Now the word "fresh" is an oxymoron here, but imagine that meat hot, fresh off the stove in a burrito? You can't get that at TB, which makes Keystone so damn important in my Taco Night. Now, as I said, this could be a huge minus, but this should let you know what you're getting with Keystone's ground beef. It's great in chili and quick spaghetti sauce. I would NOT use this for more involved recipes like lasagna, the beef crumbles are very small. My issue with Keystone is that it is insanely expensive. I would only use it if: Like in the past when I had no kitchen or refrigeration. It was just me and my trusty electric skillet. Quick meal emergencies - keep it for those desperate pinches. Emergency/prepper kits. Camping. Quick meal kits like Chicken-, Turkey-, Hamburger Helper.

If you are like me, weak willed, and lack of thawed meat at dinner hurts your wallet bc no meat = carryout, then Keystone is for you. I buy it to allow myself NO EXCUSES for delivery or eating out because after delivery and tip, you could have bought another meal.
